---
// FAQ Section
// Collapsible accordion with 6 questions
---

<section
  class="py-16 md:py-24 px-4"
  style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-rich-earth) 0%, var(--color-dark) 100%);"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2
      class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-12 text-center"
      style="color: var(--color-alabaster);"
    >
      FAQ
    </h2>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <!-- Question 1 -->
      <details
        class="rounded-xl border border-[rgba(241,237,233,0.08)] hover:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.15)] [&[open]]:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.3)] transition-all"
        style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); backdrop-filter: blur(20px);"
      >
        <summary
          class="px-6 py-6 lg:px-8 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4 text-lg font-bold list-none"
          style="color: var(--color-alabaster);"
        >
          <span>Is this another streak-tracking app?</span>
          <svg
            class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform [details[open]>&]:rotate-180"
            style="color: var(--color-jade);"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div
          class="px-6 pb-6 lg:px-8 text-base leading-relaxed"
          style="color: var(--color-faded-khaki);"
        >
          <p>
            No. Streak apps make you feel like shit when you miss a day. NooLife
            tracks your identity transformation. We gamify discipline so it's
            actually rewarding to show up. Miss a day? Your progress doesn't
            vanish, but you will see exactly how it affects your rating.
            Accountability without the guilt trip.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 2 -->
      <details
        class="rounded-xl border border-[rgba(241,237,233,0.08)] hover:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.15)] [&[open]]:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.3)] transition-all"
        style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); backdrop-filter: blur(20px);"
      >
        <summary
          class="px-6 py-6 lg:px-8 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4 text-lg font-bold list-none"
          style="color: var(--color-alabaster);"
        >
          <span>What if I miss a day?</span>
          <svg
            class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform [details[open]>&]:rotate-180"
            style="color: var(--color-jade);"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div
          class="px-6 pb-6 lg:px-8 text-base leading-relaxed"
          style="color: var(--color-faded-khaki);"
        >
          <p>
            You get back up. That's it. We track momentum, not perfection. One
            missed day doesn't erase 20 good ones. But here's the deal: your
            rating will reflect it. Your streak might break. The app doesn't
            coddle you, but it also doesn't reset you to zero like you're
            starting over. Real life happens. Winners adapt and keep moving.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 3 -->
      <details
        class="rounded-xl border border-[rgba(241,237,233,0.08)] hover:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.15)] [&[open]]:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.3)] transition-all"
        style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); backdrop-filter: blur(20px);"
      >
        <summary
          class="px-6 py-6 lg:px-8 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4 text-lg font-bold list-none"
          style="color: var(--color-alabaster);"
        >
          <span>Can I customize my habits?</span>
          <svg
            class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform [details[open]>&]:rotate-180"
            style="color: var(--color-jade);"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div
          class="px-6 pb-6 lg:px-8 text-base leading-relaxed"
          style="color: var(--color-faded-khaki);"
        >
          <p>
            Yes. We recommend 8 core habits based on research, but you control
            intensity levels, timing, and can add from our library of 16 total
            options. That said - if you skip the hard ones (cold showers, early
            wake-ups), you're only cheating yourself. Your rating knows the
            difference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 6 -->
      <details
        class="rounded-xl border border-[rgba(241,237,233,0.08)] hover:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.15)] [&[open]]:border-[rgba(0,208,156,0.3)] transition-all"
        style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); backdrop-filter: blur(20px);"
      >
        <summary
          class="px-6 py-6 lg:px-8 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4 text-lg font-bold list-none"
          style="color: var(--color-alabaster);"
        >
          <span>What happens after 66 days?</span>
          <svg
            class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform [details[open]>&]:rotate-180"
            style="color: var(--color-jade);"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div
          class="px-6 pb-6 lg:px-8 text-base leading-relaxed"
          style="color: var(--color-faded-khaki);"
        >
          <p>
            You're a different person. The habits are automatic. Your identity
            has changed. You can keep tracking, start a new 66-day arc with
            different habits, or just maintain what you've built. Most people?
            They start another arc. Because once you see what 66 days of
            discipline does, you don't want to go back to average.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
